It was in 2009 that my friend and now business partner James Ramsey alerted me to the location of a pretty spectacular site , This is the former trolley terminal that was the depot for passengers traveling over the Williamsburg Bridge from Brooklyn to Manhattan , and it was open between 1908 and 1948 , just around the time when my grandparents were living right in the area .
